## Summary: User Message DOM Structure & Rendering in Moltis Web UI

Based on my analysis of the codebase, here's the complete picture of how user messages are rendered in the DOM:

### 1. **Message Creation - DOM Structure**

**File:** `/Users/penso/.superset/worktrees/moltis/power-euphonium/crates/web/src/assets/js/chat-ui.js`

The core function that creates user messages is `chatAddMsg()` (lines 31-49):

```javascript
export function chatAddMsg(cls, content, isHtml) {
	if (!S.chatMsgBox) return null;
	clearChatEmptyState();
	var el = document.createElement("div");
	el.className = `msg ${cls}`;  // Creates: <div class="msg user">
	if (cls === "system") {
		el.classList.add("system-notice");
	}
	if (isHtml) {
		el.innerHTML = content;  // Rendered markdown HTML
	} else {
		el.textContent = content;  // Plain text
	}
	S.chatMsgBox.appendChild(el);
	if (!S.chatBatchLoading) S.chatMsgBox.scrollTop = S.chatMsgBox.scrollHeight;
	return el;
}
```

For messages with images, use `chatAddMsgWithImages()` (lines 58-86):

```javascript
export function chatAddMsgWithImages(cls, htmlContent, images) {
	// Creates: <div class="msg user">
	//   <div>rendered HTML text</div>
	//   <div class="msg-image-row">
	//     <img class="msg-image-thumb" />
	//   </div>
	// </div>
```

### 2. **User Message Sending - page-chat.js**

**File:** `/Users/penso/.superset/worktrees/moltis/power-euphonium/crates/web/src/assets/js/page-chat.js`

The `buildChatMessage()` function (lines 1180-1198) creates the user message element:

```javascript
function buildChatMessage(text, seq, displayText) {
	var userText = displayText !== undefined ? displayText : text;
	var images = hasPendingImages() ? getPendingImages() : [];

	// With images: calls chatAddMsgWithImages("user", ...)
	// Without images: calls chatAddMsg("user", renderMarkdown(userText), true)

	return { params: params, el: el };
}
```

**The `sendChat()` function (lines 1201-1228)** is the main entry point:
- Calls `buildChatMessage()` to create the DOM element
- Appends to chat DOM immediately via `chatAddMsg()` or `chatAddMsgWithImages()`
- Sends RPC `"chat.send"` message to server

### 3. **DOM Structure - Exact Selectors for E2E Tests**

**User message structure:**

```html
<div class="msg user">
  <div><!-- Rendered markdown content --></div>
  <!-- Optional: image row for attachments -->
  <div class="msg-image-row">
    <img class="msg-image-thumb" src="data:..." alt="image name" />
  </div>
</div>
```

**Parent container:** The chat message box is `#chatMsgBox` (or accessed via `S.chatMsgBox`).

**CSS Classes for styling:** (from `/crates/web/src/assets/css/chat.css`)

- `.msg` - Base message class (line 40)
- `.msg.user` - User message styling (lines 51-56):
  - Background: `var(--user-bg)`
  - Border: `1px solid var(--user-border)`
  - Alignment: `align-self: flex-end` (right-aligned)
- `.msg.assistant` - Assistant messages (lines 58-62) for comparison
- `.msg.system` - System messages (lines 66-72)

### 4. **Rendering from History - sessions.js**

**File:** `/Users/penso/.superset/worktrees/moltis/power-euphonium/crates/web/src/assets/js/sessions.js`

The `renderHistoryUserMessage()` function (lines 642-687) renders saved user messages:

```javascript
function renderHistoryUserMessage(msg) {
	var text = "";
	var images = [];
	// Parse multimodal content (text + images from history)
	if (Array.isArray(msg.content)) {
		var parsed = parseMultimodalContent(msg.content);
		text = msg.channel ? stripChannelPrefix(parsed.text) : parsed.text;
		images = parsed.images;
	} else {
		text = msg.channel ? stripChannelPrefix(msg.content || "") : msg.content || "";
	}

	// Calls either chatAddMsg() or chatAddMsgWithImages() depending on content
	if (msg.audio) {
		el = chatAddMsg("user", "", true);
		// Add audio player + text...
	} else if (images.length > 0) {
		el = chatAddMsgWithImages("user", text ? renderMarkdown(text) : "", images);
	} else {
		el = chatAddMsg("user", renderMarkdown(text), true);
	}
	if (el && msg.channel) appendChannelFooter(el, msg.channel);
	return el;
}
```

The main `renderHistory()` function (lines 1266-1313) iterates through history and calls `renderHistoryUserMessage()` for `msg.role === "user"`.

### 5. **E2E Test Helpers**

**File:** `/Users/penso/.superset/worktrees/moltis/power-euphonium/crates/web/ui/e2e/helpers.js`

Available helpers for writing tests:
- `navigateAndWait(page, path)` - Navigate to chat and wait for content
- `createSession(page)` - Create a new session
- `watchPageErrors(page)` - Capture JS errors
- `waitForWsConnected(page)` - Wait for WebSocket ready

### 6. **Key DOM Elements & Attributes**

For e2e tests, use these selectors:

```javascript
// User message elements
page.locator(".msg.user")                    // All user messages
page.locator(".msg.user").first()            // First user message
page.locator(".msg.user").nth(0)             // By index

// User message with images
page.locator(".msg.user .msg-image-row")    // Image container
page.locator(".msg.user .msg-image-thumb")  // Individual images

// Chat container
page.locator("#chatMsgBox")                  // Message container div

// User message text (rendered HTML)
page.locator(".msg.user").getByText(/your text/i)
```

### 7. **Message Content Structure**

- Plain text messages: `renderMarkdown(text)` escapes and converts to HTML
- Image messages: Multimodal content with `.msg-image-row` and `.msg-image-thumb`
- Audio messages: Audio player inside `.msg` with optional text below
- Channel messages: Additional `.msg-channel-footer` appended

The exact HTML looks like:

```html
<div id="chatMsgBox" class="flex flex-col gap-3 ...">
  <div class="msg user">
    <div>rendered HTML</div>
  </div>
  <div class="msg assistant">
    <div>assistant response</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

This is everything you need to write e2e tests for user message rendering!

